====Usage notes====
This term is promoted along with the idea that what has previously been termed {{m|en|prostitution}} should be recognized as work on equal terms with that of conventional jobs, with the legal implications this has. It is sometimes regarded as a less offensive alternative to {{m|en|prostitute}}, although "sex worker" has a much broader meaning.

